body:
This diff is comparing "join" method in LooperThread class with a golden file. LooperThread inherits from Python's threading.Thread (https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/python/training/coordinator.py). So, the "join" method here is just "join" in threading.Thread.

We really shouldn't be comparing arguments of a Python method though (that is, this shouldn't be a part of our golden file). I will look into fixing it. 

Can you revert changes to tensorflow.train.-looper-thread.pbtxt for now? I can re-trigger the builds once you do. Also, which Python version are you using?
